main event: On January 22, 1952 near Larson AFB in Moses Lake, Washington, a green disk-shaped object, the size of a large weather balloon, was observed by at least 63 reliable witnesses from a fighter interceptor squadron. The object decreased in size until disappearing and no sound was heard during the sighting.
interesting points: At least 63 reliable witnesses, including personnel from a fighter interceptor squadron, observed the green disk-shaped object.
The object decreased in size until disappearing and no sound was heard during the sighting.
The object was seen at an altitude of about 12,000 feet, below a high cloud layer.

An unidentified flying object was reported on 3 January 1953 at Moses Lake Air Force Base in Washington. The object was observed for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes and was traveling at high speeds, making sudden stops, and changing direction at very short intervals.

Descriptions of the object varied, ranging from circular, rectangular, to cylindrical in shape, with a reported size of approximately 30 to 50 feet in length and 10 to 15 feet in width, and a silver or metallic appearance.
